│ false;\n}\n```\n\n**Proposed Change:**\n```cpp\n  // Check if the bundle is profitable  │
│ and scheduleable.\n  BS.reset();\n  if (!BS.tryScheduleBundle(Bundle->getScalars(),     │
│ this, Insts, Edge))\n    return false;\n}\n```\nBy inserting `BS.reset();`, we          │
│ guarantee that every call to `tryScheduleBundle` operates on a clean, properly          │
│ initialized scheduler state, thus resolving the state corruption bug.\n\n### 5.         │
│ Conclusion\n\nThe crash is caused by a state management bug where the scheduler's       │
│ context was not reset after a failed scheduling attempt during the recursive            │
│ tree-building process. Adding a call to `BlockScheduling::reset()` before each          │
│ scheduling attempt ensures that the scheduler's state is always clean, preventing the   │
│ corruption that leads to the assertion failure. This makes the SLP vectorizer more      │
│ robust when exploring complex vectorization candidates."})                              │
