│ ### Analysis of the Bug                                                                 │
│                                                                                         │
│ The provided information indicates a crash in the SLP Vectorizer. The root cause        │
│ analysis is very clear: the `BlockScheduling` object, which is used to determine if a   │
│ bundle of instructions can be vectorized and scheduled, is not being reset between      │
│ different scheduling attempts within the recursive `buildTreeRec` function.             │
│                                                                                         │
│ When `tryScheduleBundle` is called and fails, it leaves the `BlockScheduling` object in │
│ a partially modified state. A subsequent call to `tryScheduleBundle` on the same        │
│ object, but for a different bundle, inherits this corrupted state. This leads to        │
│ incorrect dependency counting and eventually triggers the assertion                     │
│ `hasValidDependencies()`.                                                               │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### Proposed Fix                                                                        │
│                                                                                         │
│ The fix is to call the `reset()` method on the `BlockScheduling` object (`BS`) before   │
│ each call to `tryScheduleBundle` inside `BoUpSLP::buildTreeRec`. This will ensure that  │
│ every scheduling attempt starts with a clean state, preventing the state corruption     │
│ that causes the crash.                                                                  │
│                                                                                         │
